cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a novel module for improving image classification using convolutional neural networks. As such, it is likely to fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the decision-making process in classification networks, which could also place it under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of neural networks for classification also suggests the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image data, which could place it under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
